16 §1961. Purpose
17 The purpose of this Part is to regulate the trade practices and affairs of any
18 person engaged in the business of insurance, in accordance with the intent of
19 congress as expressed in Public Law 15-79th Congress*, by defining or providing
20 for the determination of all acts, methods, and practices which constitute unfair
21 methods of competition and unfair or deceptive acts and practices in this state, and
22 to prohibit the same.
23 §1962. Definitions
24 When used in this Part: For purposes of this Part, the following definitions
25 apply:
26 * * *
27 G.(1) "Business of insurance" means any of the following:
28 (a) An action concerning the sale, advertisement, or solicitation of a contract
29 or policy of insurance.
